    <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Orlando has some genuinely walkable pockets if you know where to look.</p><h2>Winter Park</h2><p>Park Avenue is the gold standard.</p><ul><li>Rollins College</li><li>Farmer's market</li></ul><p>Here's a photo:</p><img src="https://picsum.photos/seed/winterpark/800/500" alt="Winter Park" /><h2>Baldwin Park</h2><p>Built around a chain of lakes with a true town center.</p>]]></content:encoded>
    <excerpt:encoded><![CDATA[Nine Orlando neighborhoods where you can genuinely leave the car at home.]]></excerpt:encoded>
